ai_flow.endpoint.server.exception module¶

exception ai_flow.endpoint.server.exception.AIFlowException(error_msg, error_code=1, **kwargs)[source]¶

Bases: Exception

Generic exception thrown to surface failure information about external-facing operations. The error message associated with this exception may be exposed to clients in HTTP responses for debugging purposes. If the error text is sensitive, raise a generic Exception object instead.

Parameters

  • message – The message describing the error that occured. This will be included in the exception’s serialized JSON representation.

  • error_code – An appropriate error code for the error that occured; it will be included in the exception’s serialized JSON representation. This should be one of the codes listed in the ai_flow.endpoint.proto.message_pb2 proto.

  • kwargs – Additional key-value pairs to include in the serialized JSON representation of the AIFlowException.

shutdown(wait=True)[source]¶

Clean-up the resources associated with the Executor.

It is safe to call this method several times. Otherwise, no other methods can be called after this one.

Args:
wait: If True then shutdown will not return until all running

futures have finished executing and the resources used by the executor have been reclaimed.

ai_flow.endpoint.server.server_runner module¶

class ai_flow.endpoint.server.server_runner.AIFlowServerRunner(config_file: Optional[str] = None, enable_ha=False, server_uri: Optional[str] = None, ttl_ms=10000)[source]¶

Bases: object

AI flow server runner. This class is the runner class for the AIFlowServer. It parse the server configuration and manage the live cycle of the AIFlowServer.

Set the server attribute according to the server config file.

Parameters

config_file – server configuration file.

start(is_block=False) → None[source]¶

Start the AI flow runner.

Parameters

is_block – AI flow runner will run non-stop if True.

stop(clear_sql_lite_db_file=True) → None[source]¶

Stop the AI flow runner.

Parameters

clear_sql_lite_db_file – If True, the sqlite database files will be deleted When the server stops working.
